    "Assumption 1 (Constraint span and realization).",
    "For any x ∈ X, {g(x, y)} y ∈ Y is a span of the vector space R m, and there exists a response y ∈ Y such that g(x, y) = 0.Assumption 1 first requires that there exist m responses {y i ∈ Y} m i = 1 such that the constraint functions {g(x, y i)} m i = 1 are linearly independent.",
    "This can be easily satisfied since the language space is large and the constraint functions are nonlinear.",
    "It is mild to have g(x, y) = 0 as we can always translate the constraint functions so that they equal zero at specific responses.",
    "Lemma 1 (Convexity and smoothness of dual function)."
